{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775908285752,"sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","part":{"id":"prt_d7c61d9b500176GBqOylu96PgQ","messageID":"msg_d7c61ceb4001G94OLGS0wFyu67","sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029 Design: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: ## Architecture\n4: \n5: ```\n6: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n7: │                     HTTP Client Layer                            │\n8: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐                      │\n9: │  │   HTTPClient     │  │ AsyncHTTPClient  │                      │\n10: │  │   (Sync + Async) │  │   (Async Only)   │                      │\n11: │  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘                      │\n12: │           └─────────────────────┘                                │\n13: │                         │                                        │\n14: │  ┌──────────────────────┴──────────────────────┐                │\n15: │  │              Transport Layer                │                │\n16: │  │  ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐   │                │\n17: │  │  │ Connection│ │  Retry   │ │   Auth   │   │                │\n18: │  │  │  Pool     │ │  Logic   │ │Middleware│   │                │\n19: │  │  └──────────┘ └──────────┘ └──────────┘   │                │\n20: │  │  ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐   │                │\n21: │  │  │ Request  │ │ Response │ │  Hooks   │   │                │\n22: │  │  │ Builder  │ │ Wrapper  │ │          │   │                │\n23: │  │  └──────────┘ └──────────┘ └──────────┘   │                │\n24: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────┘                │\n25: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n26:                               │\n27:                               ▼\n28:                     ┌─────────────────┐\n29:                     │   HTTP Server   │\n30:                     └─────────────────┘\n31: ```\n32: \n33: ## Design Principles\n34: \n35: 1. **Unified API**: Same interface for sync and async operations\n36: 2. **Composability**: Middleware pattern for extensibility\n37: 3. **Resource Management**: Proper connection pooling and cleanup\n38: 4. **Fail-Fast**: Clear exceptions with contextual information\n39: 5. **Observability**: Request/response logging and metrics hooks\n40: \n41: ## Class Design\n42: \n43: ### HTTPClient\n44: \n45: ```python\n46: class HTTPClient:\n47:     \"\"\"Unified HTTP client with sync and async support.\"\"\"\n48:     \n49:     def __init__(\n50:         self,\n51:         base_url: str = \"\",\n52:         auth: Optional[AuthMiddleware] = None,\n53:         timeout: float = 30.0,\n54:         retry_config: Optional[RetryConfig] = None,\n55:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n56:     ):\n57:         ...\n58:     \n59:     def request(self, method: str, path: str, **kwargs) -> Response:\n60:         \"\"\"Make a synchronous HTTP request.\"\"\"\n61:         ...\n62:     \n63:     async def arequest(self, method: str, path: str, **kwargs) -> Response:\n64:         \"\"\"Make an asynchronous HTTP request.\"\"\"\n65:         ...\n66:     \n67:     def close(self) -> None:\n68:         \"\"\"Close sync client and connection pool.\"\"\"\n69:         ...\n70:     \n71:     async def aclose(self) -> None:\n72:         \"\"\"Close async client and connection pool.\"\"\"\n73:         ...\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Auth Middleware\n77: \n78: ```python\n79: class AuthMiddleware(ABC):\n80:     \"\"\"Base class for authentication middleware.\"\"\"\n81:     \n82:     @abstractmethod\n83:     def apply(self, request: Request) -> Request:\n84:         \"\"\"Apply authentication to the request.\"\"\"\n85:         ...\n86: \n87: class BearerTokenAuth(AuthMiddleware):\n88:     \"\"\"Bearer token authentication.\"\"\"\n89:     \n90:     def __init__(self, token: str):\n91:         self.token = token\n92:     \n93:     def apply(self, request: Request) -> Request:\n94:         request.headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {self.token}\"\n95:         return request\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### Retry Strategy\n99: \n100: ```python\n101: class RetryConfig:\n102:     \"\"\"Configuration for retry behavior.\"\"\"\n103:     \n104:     max_attempts: int = 3\n105:     strategy: RetryStrategy = RetryStrategy.EXPONENTIAL\n106:     base_delay: float = 1.0\n107:     max_delay: float = 60.0\n108:     retryable_status_codes: Set[int] = {429, 500, 502, 503, 504}\n109:     retryable_exceptions: Set[Type[Exception]] = {ConnectionError, TimeoutError}\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ## Data Flow\n113: \n114: 1. User calls `client.get(\"/api/resource\")`\n115: 2. Request builder constructs full URL and headers\n116: 3. Auth middleware adds authentication headers\n117: 4. Retry wrapper executes request with retry logic\n118: 5. HTTPX client sends request through connection pool\n119: 6. Response wrapper processes HTTPX response\n120: 7. Result or exception returned to user\n121: \n122: ## Error Handling Strategy\n123: \n124: - Network errors → `ConnectionError`\n125: - Timeout errors → `TimeoutError`\n126: - 4xx errors → `ClientError` (with specific subclasses)\n127: - 5xx errors → `ServerError` (retryable by default)\n128: - Redirect errors → `RedirectError`\n\n(End of file - total 128 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029 Design: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     HTTP Client Layer                            │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐                      │\n│  │   HTTPClient     │  │ AsyncHTTPClient  │                      │\n│  │   (Sync + Async) │  │   (Async Only)   │                      │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘                      │\n│           └─────────────────────┘                                │\n│                         │                                        │\n│  ┌──────────────────────┴──────────────────────┐                │\n│  │              Transport Layer                │                │\n│  │  ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐   │                │\n│  │  │ Connection│ │  Retry   │ │   Auth   │   │                │\n│  │  │  Pool     │ │  Logic   │ │Middleware│   │                │\n│  │  └──────────┘ └──────────┘ └──────────┘   │                │\n│  │  ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐   │                │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/design.md","time":{"start":1775908285721,"end":1775908285751}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775908285754,"sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","part":{"id":"prt_d7c61de730017rUpk0P1PQlE6Q","messageID":"msg_d7c61ceb4001G94OLGS0wFyu67","sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029 Implementation Plan: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: ## Phase 1: Foundation (Day 1)\n4: \n5: ### Tasks\n6: 1. **Setup project structure**\n7:    - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/` directory\n8:    - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/__init__.py`\n9:    - Create module structure files\n10: \n11: 2. **Define configuration models**\n12:    - Implement `HTTPClientConfig` model\n13:    - Implement `RetryConfig` model\n14:    - Define `RetryStrategy` enum\n15: \n16: 3. **Implement exception hierarchy**\n17:    - Create base `HTTPError`\n18:    - Create specific exception classes\n19:    - Add HTTP status code mapping\n20: \n21: ## Phase 2: Core HTTP Client (Day 1-2)\n22: \n23: ### Tasks\n24: 1. **Implement request builder**\n25:    - Create `Request` dataclass\n26:    - Create `RequestBuilder` with URL construction\n27:    - Add header normalization\n28: \n29: 2. **Implement response wrapper**\n30:    - Create `Response` class\n31:    - Add JSON parsing helper\n32:    - Add error detection\n33: \n34: 3. **Implement authentication middleware**\n35:    - Create `AuthMiddleware` base class\n36:    - Implement `APIKeyAuth`\n37:    - Implement `BearerTokenAuth`\n38: \n39: 4. **Implement retry logic**\n40:    - Create retry decorator/policies\n41:    - Configure exponential backoff\n42:    - Define retryable vs non-retryable errors\n43: \n44: ## Phase 3: HTTP Client Implementation (Day 2)\n45: \n46: ### Tasks\n47: 1. **Implement HTTPClient class**\n48:    - Create `HTTPClient` class\n49:    - Implement sync request methods (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)\n50:    - Add context manager support\n51: \n52: 2. **Implement AsyncHTTPClient**\n53:    - Create `AsyncHTTPClient` class\n54:    - Implement async request methods\n55:    - Add async context manager support\n56: \n57: 3. **Add connection pooling**\n58:    - Configure HTTPX connection limits\n59:    - Implement keep-alive handling\n60:    - Add connection cleanup\n61: \n62: ## Phase 4: Testing & Documentation (Day 3)\n63: \n64: ### Tasks\n65: 1. **Unit tests**\n66:    - Test client initialization\n67:    - Test request building\n68:    - Test response handling\n69:    - Test retry logic\n70:    - Test auth middleware\n71:    - Mock transport layer\n72: \n73: 2. **Integration tests**\n74:    - Test against mock server\n75:    - Test error scenarios\n76:    - Test timeout handling\n77: \n78: 3. **Documentation**\n79:    - Add docstrings to all public APIs\n80:    - Create usage examples\n81:    - Write README section\n82: \n83: ## Dependencies\n84: \n85: ```\n86: sdk-python/\n87: ├── src/agentcube/\n88: │   └── http/\n89: │       ├── __init__.py\n90: │       ├── client.py\n91: │       ├── request.py\n92: │       ├── response.py\n93: │       ├── auth.py\n94: │       ├── retry.py\n95: │       └── exceptions.py\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ## Risk Mitigation\n99: \n100: - Use established library (httpx) for HTTP operations\n101: - Follow existing project patterns\n102: - Regular testing during development\n103: - Handle edge cases (timeouts, redirects, SSL)\n\n(End of file - total 103 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029 Implementation Plan: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation (Day 1)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Setup project structure**\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/` directory\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/__init__.py`\n   - Create module structure files\n\n2. **Define configuration models**\n   - Implement `HTTPClientConfig` model\n   - Implement `RetryConfig` model\n   - Define `RetryStrategy` enum\n\n3. **Implement exception hierarchy**\n   - Create base `HTTPError`\n   - Create specific exception classes\n   - Add HTTP status code mapping\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/plan.md","time":{"start":1775908285724,"end":1775908285753}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775908285756,"sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","part":{"id":"prt_d7c61e3590014MEFApy8oYmEki","messageID":"msg_d7c61ceb4001G94OLGS0wFyu67","sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-029  \n6: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: **Base Spec:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n10: \n11: AR-029 implements the low-level HTTP client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK. This includes the `ControlPlaneClient` for Workload Manager API communication, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Router data plane operations, and supporting utilities for HTTP session management, authentication, and timeout handling.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: HTTP Session Factory\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a `create_session` utility function that constructs a `requests.Session` with connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` protocols.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Session created with default pool settings\n22: - **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called without arguments\n23: - **WHEN** the session is constructed\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL mount HTTPAdapter for both protocols with `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Session created with custom pool settings\n27: - **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is called\n28: - **WHEN** the session is constructed\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided pool configuration values\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Session reused for multiple requests\n32: - **GIVEN** a session created by `create_session()`\n33: - **WHEN** multiple HTTP requests are made through the same session\n34: - **THEN** connections SHALL be reused from the pool\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ### Requirement: Control Plane HTTP Client\n39: \n40: The system SHALL implement `ControlPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` for Workload Manager API communication using `requests.Session` with connection pooling.\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Create session POST request\n43: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)` is called\n44: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\": \"...\", \"namespace\": \"...\", \"ttl\": ..., \"metadata\": ...}`\n46: - **AND** it SHALL return `data[\"sessionId\"]` from the response\n47: - **AND** if `sessionId` is missing, it SHALL raise `ValueError`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Delete session with 404 handling\n50: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)` is called\n51: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n52: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (idempotent behavior)\n53: - **AND** on other failures, it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL resolution\n56: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` argument is not provided\n57: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n58: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Authentication token resolution\n61: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` argument is not provided\n62: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL attempt to read token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`\n64: - **AND** if token is non-empty, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header on the session\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Default headers on session\n67: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized\n68: - **WHEN** the session is created\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL have `Content-Type: application/json` as a default header\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Timeout tuple on requests\n72: - **GIVEN** `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0`\n73: - **WHEN** any request is made\n74: - **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, timeout)` = `(5.0, 120)`\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter Data Plane HTTP Client\n79: \n80: The system SHALL implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` for Router data plane operations.\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Base URL construction from router URL\n83: - **GIVEN** `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name` are provided\n84: - **WHEN** `base_url` is not explicitly provided\n85: - **THEN** it SHALL construct base URL as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Execute command POST\n88: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)` is called\n89: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n90: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}api/execute` with JSON body `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`\n91: - **AND** if `exit_code != 0` in response, raise `CommandExecutionError`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Execute timeout buffer\n94: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with `timeout=60`\n95: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n96: - **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `60 + 2.0 = 62.0` seconds (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Write file POST\n99: - **GIVEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n100: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n101: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": \"...\", \"content\": \"base64...\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Upload file multipart\n104: - **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n105: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n106: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}api/files` with multipart/form-data\n107: - **AND** include `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path': ..., 'mode': '0644'}`\n108: - **AND** include `x-agentcube-session-id` header explicitly (no JSON Content-Type on outer request)\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: Download file GET\n111: - **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` is called\n112: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n113: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET {base_url}api/files/{clean_path}` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n114: - **AND** use `stream=True` for the response\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: List files GET\n117: - **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\".\")` is called\n118: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n119: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET {base_url}api/files?path={path}`\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Session header on all requests\n122: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with `session_id`\n123: - **WHEN** any `_request` method is called\n124: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ### Requirement: Agent Runtime Data Plane HTTP Client\n129: \n130: The system SHALL implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` for Agent Runtime Router invocations.\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Base URL construction\n133: - **GIVEN** `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name` are provided\n134: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL construct base URL as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID\n138: - **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n139: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET {base_url}` and read response header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n141: - **AND** if the header is missing, raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Invoke POST with headers\n144: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=None)` is called\n145: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n146: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST {base_url}` with:\n147:   - Header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n148:   - Header `Content-Type: application/json`\n149:   - JSON body from `payload` dict\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n152: - **GIVEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout` argument\n153: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n154: - **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: SESSION_HEADER constant\n157: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n158: - **WHEN** accessing the class constant\n159: - **THEN** `SESSION_HEADER` SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ### Requirement: Timeout Behavior\n164: \n165: The system SHALL implement consistent timeout defaults across all HTTP clients.\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Control plane default timeouts\n168: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout overrides\n169: - **WHEN** requests are made\n170: - **THEN** connect timeout SHALL default to `5.0` seconds\n171: - **AND** read timeout SHALL default to `120` seconds\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Data plane default timeouts\n174: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` or `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout overrides\n175: - **WHEN** requests are made\n176: - **THEN** connect timeout SHALL default to `5.0` seconds\n177: - **AND** read timeout SHALL default to `120` seconds\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Per-request timeout override\n180: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=30)` is called\n181: - **WHEN** the request is made\n182: - **THEN** the effective read timeout SHALL be `30 + 2.0 = 32.0` seconds\n183: - **AND** the PicoD timeout string SHALL be `\"30s\"`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Constructor timeout override\n186: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0)` is constructed\n187: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without timeout argument\n188: - **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(3.0, 60)`\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ### Requirement: Session Header Management\n193: \n194: The system SHALL consistently use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Router data plane requests.\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header default\n197: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with `session_id`\n198: - **WHEN** the session is created\n199: - **THEN** the default headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Agent Runtime session header constant\n202: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n203: - **WHEN** the `SESSION_HEADER` constant is used\n204: - **THEN** it SHALL be `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Upload sets header explicitly\n207: - **GIVEN** `upload_file` performs a multipart upload\n208: - **WHEN** the request is constructed\n209: - **THEN** the `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be set explicitly on the request (not relying on session defaults)\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ### Requirement: Connection Pool Configuration\n214: \n215: The system SHALL support configurable connection pooling for all HTTP clients.\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Default pool configuration\n218: - **GIVEN** any HTTP client is initialized without pool overrides\n219: - **WHEN** the session is created\n220: - **THEN** `pool_connections` SHALL default to `10`\n221: - **AND** `pool_maxsize` SHALL default to `10`\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Custom pool configuration\n224: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is constructed\n225: - **WHEN** the session is created\n226: - **THEN** the HTTPAdapter SHALL be configured with the custom pool settings\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Pool settings passed through create_session\n229: - **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=50)` is called\n230: - **WHEN** the session is returned\n231: - **THEN** the underlying adapter pool SHALL reflect these settings\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## Interface\n236: \n237: ### ControlPlaneClient\n238: \n239: | Method | Parameters | Returns | Description |\n240: |--------|------------|---------|-------------|\n241: | `__init__` | `workload_manager_url=None, auth_token=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0, pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Initialize with URL/auth resolution |\n242: | `create_session` | `name=\"my-interpreter\", namespace=\"default\", metadata=None, ttl=3600` | `str` | POST to create session, return sessionId |\n243: | `delete_session` | `session_id: str` | `bool` | DELETE session, True on success/404 |\n244: | `close` | - | `None` | Close the HTTP session |\n245: \n246: ### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n247: \n248: | Method | Parameters | Returns | Description |\n249: |--------|------------|---------|-------------|\n250: | `__init__` | `session_id, router_url=None, namespace=None, cr_name=None, base_url=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0, pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Initialize with session and URL |\n251: | `_request` | `method, endpoint, body=None, **kwargs` | `Response` | Internal request method with headers |\n252: | `execute_command` | `command, timeout=None` | `str` | POST api/execute, return stdout |\n253: | `run_code` | `language, code, timeout=None` | `str` | Write file and execute |\n254: | `write_file` | `content, remote_path` | `None` | POST api/files with base64 content |\n255: | `upload_file` | `local_path, remote_path` | `None` | POST multipart api/files |\n256: | `download_file` | `remote_path, local_path` | `None` | GET api/files/{path} with streaming |\n257: | `list_files` | `path=\".\"` | `Any` | GET api/files?path={path} |\n258: | `close` | - | `None` | Close the HTTP session |\n259: \n260: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n261: \n262: | Method | Parameters | Returns | Description |\n263: |--------|------------|---------|-------------|\n264: | `__init__` | `router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0, pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Initialize with Router endpoint |\n265: | `bootstrap_session_id` | - | `str` | GET base URL, return session header |\n266: | `invoke` | `session_id, payload, timeout=None` | `Response` | POST JSON with session header |\n267: | `close` | - | `None` | Close the HTTP session |\n268: \n269: ### Utility Functions\n270: \n271: | Function | Location | Parameters | Returns | Description |\n272: |----------|----------|------------|---------|-------------|\n273: | `create_session` | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10` | `Session` | Create requests.Session with adapters |\n274: | `read_token_from_file` | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `file_path: str` | `str` | Read file contents stripped, \"\" on error |\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## Behavior\n279: \n280: ### HTTP Request Flow\n281: \n282: ```\n283: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n284: │  Client Call    │────▶│  Prepare Request │────▶│  Apply Headers  │\n285: └─────────────────┘     └──────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n286:                                                            │\n287:                            ┌──────────────────┐           │\n288:                            │  Parse Response  │◀──────────┘\n289:                            └──────────────────┘\n290:                                     │\n291:                            ┌────────┴────────┐\n292:                            ▼                 ▼\n293:                     ┌────────────┐    ┌────────────┐\n294:                     │  Success   │    │   Error    │\n295:                     │  Return    │    │  Raise/Log │\n296:                     │  Result    │    │  Exception │\n297:                     └────────────┘    └────────────┘\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ### Timeout Configuration Hierarchy\n301: \n302: 1. **Per-call timeout**: Method argument (e.g., `execute_command(timeout=30)`)\n303: 2. **Instance default**: Constructor value (e.g., `timeout=120`)\n304: 3. **Global default**: Module constant (`DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120`)\n305: \n306: ### Session Header Application\n307: \n308: | Client Type | Header Source | Applied Via |\n309: |-------------|---------------|-------------|\n310: | `ControlPlaneClient` | N/A | Not used (auth via Authorization) |\n311: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Constructor `session_id` | Session default headers |\n312: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Method `session_id` arg | Per-request headers |\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## Changes to Base Specification\n317: \n318: This AR implements the HTTP client layer defined in `python-sdk/spec.md` sections:\n319: - HTTP client contracts — control plane\n320: - HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n321: - HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n322: - Session header management\n323: - Timeout behavior\n324: \n325: No changes to base spec interfaces.\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ## Dependencies\n330: \n331: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n332: |---------|---------|---------|\n333: | `requests` | any | HTTP client library |\n334: | `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT token handling (for auth) |\n335: | `cryptography` | any | Crypto operations |\n336: \n337: ---\n338: \n339: ## File Index\n340: \n341: | Path | Purpose |\n342: |------|---------|\n343: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` implementation |\n344: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n345: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n346: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` HTTP session factory |\n347: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` utility |\n348: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | `CommandExecutionError` and base exceptions |\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ## Testing\n353: \n354: ### Unit Test Scenarios\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: create_session with defaults\n357: ```python\n358: session = create_session()\n359: assert session.adapters[\"http://\"].config[\"pool_connections\"] == 10\n360: assert session.adapters[\"https://\"].config[\"pool_maxsize\"] == 10\n361: ```\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: ControlPlaneClient creates session with correct timeout\n364: ```python\n365: client = ControlPlaneClient(timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0)\n366: # Verify session timeout tuple (3.0, 60) used in requests\n367: ```\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base URL\n370: ```python\n371: client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n372:     session_id=\"abc\",\n373:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n374:     namespace=\"default\",\n375:     cr_name=\"my-interpreter\"\n376: )\n377: assert client.base_url == \"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"\n378: ```\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Execute command timeout buffer\n381: ```python\n382: client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"abc\", base_url=\"http://test\")\n383: # When execute_command(command, timeout=30) is called\n384: # Read timeout should be 32.0 seconds (30 + 2.0 buffer)\n385: ```\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap session\n388: ```python\n389: client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n390:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n391:     namespace=\"default\",\n392:     agent_name=\"my-agent\"\n393: )\n394: session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n395: # Should GET base URL and extract x-agentcube-session-id header\n396: ```\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: Upload file multipart with session header\n399: ```python\n400: client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id=\"abc\", base_url=\"http://test\")\n401: client.upload_file(\"local.txt\", \"/remote/path.txt\")\n402: # Should POST multipart with x-agentcube-session-id header\n403: ```\n404: \n405: ---\n406: \n407: ## Deliverables\n408: \n409: | Path | Description |\n410: |------|-------------|\n411: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Control plane HTTP client with session management |\n412: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Code Interpreter data plane HTTP client |\n413: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Agent Runtime data plane HTTP client |\n414: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | HTTP session factory with connection pooling |\n415: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Token file reading utility |\n416: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | CommandExecutionError exception class |\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: *AR-029 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 420 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-029  \n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\nAR-029 implements the low-level HTTP client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK. This includes the `ControlPlaneClient` for Workload Manager API communication, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Router data plane operations, and supporting utilities for HTTP session management, authentication, and timeout handling.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: HTTP Session Factory\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `create_session` utility function that constructs a `requests.Session` with connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` protocols.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775908285726,"end":1775908285755}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775908285760,"sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","part":{"id":"prt_d7c61e84a0017sueSqnmp1y9fu","messageID":"msg_d7c61ceb4001G94OLGS0wFyu67","sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: > **AR ID:** AR-029\n4: > **Module:** `sdk-python`\n5: > **Language:** Python\n6: > **Size:** M\n7: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: Implement the low-level HTTP client foundation for the sdk-python module. This component provides a robust, reusable HTTP client layer that handles connection management, request/response handling, authentication, retry logic, and error handling. It serves as the transport foundation for all high-level SDK clients.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-3.1 — Project Structure Setup\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 3.1.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/` directory | Directory exists | 0.1h |\n22: | 3.1.2 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/__init__.py` | File exists with exports | 0.1h |\n23: | 3.1.3 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/client.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n24: | 3.1.4 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/request.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n25: | 3.1.5 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/response.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n26: | 3.1.6 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/auth.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n27: | 3.1.7 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/retry.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n28: | 3.1.8 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/exceptions.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n29: \n30: **Deliverable:** Project structure ready for implementation.\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## ST-3.2 — Configuration Models\n35: \n36: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n37: |---|------|--------------|------|\n38: | 3.2.1 | Create `HTTPClientConfig` Pydantic model | base_url, timeout, headers fields | 0.5h |\n39: | 3.2.2 | Add connection pool settings to config | max_connections, max_keepalive | 0.25h |\n40: | 3.2.3 | Add SSL verification options | verify_ssl, ssl_cert fields | 0.25h |\n41: | 3.2.4 | Create `RetryConfig` Pydantic model | max_attempts, strategy fields | 0.5h |\n42: | 3.2.5 | Define `RetryStrategy` enum | EXPONENTIAL, LINEAR, FIXED | 0.25h |\n43: | 3.2.6 | Add retryable status codes config | retryable_status_codes: Set[int] | 0.25h |\n44: | 3.2.7 | Add JSON schema export for configs | `.model_json_schema()` works | 0.25h |\n45: \n46: **Deliverable:** Configuration models defined with validation.\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## ST-3.3 — Exception Hierarchy\n51: \n52: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n53: |---|------|--------------|------|\n54: | 3.3.1 | Implement `HTTPError` base exception | Base class with message, code attrs | 0.25h |\n55: | 3.3.2 | Implement `ConnectionError` (network) | Raised on transport failures | 0.25h |\n56: | 3.3.3 | Implement `TimeoutError` (timeout) | Raised on request timeout | 0.25h |\n57: | 3.3.4 | Implement `RedirectError` (redirects) | Raised on redirect errors | 0.25h |\n58: | 3.3.5 | Implement `StatusCodeError` (4xx/5xx) | Base for HTTP status errors | 0.25h |\n59: | 3.3.6 | Implement `ClientError` (4xx) subclass | BadRequest, Unauthorized, etc. | 0.5h |\n60: | 3.3.7 | Implement `ServerError` (5xx) subclass | Server errors, retryable | 0.25h |\n61: | 3.3.8 | Add HTTP status code mapping | status_code -> exception class | 0.25h |\n62: | 3.3.9 | Export all exceptions from `exceptions.py` | Import works | 0.1h |\n63: \n64: **Deliverable:** Exception hierarchy defined and exportable.\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## ST-3.4 — Request Builder\n69: \n70: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n71: |---|------|--------------|------|\n72: | 3.4.1 | Create `Request` dataclass | method, url, headers, body fields | 0.25h |\n73: | 3.4.2 | Create `RequestBuilder` class | Builder pattern implementation | 0.25h |\n74: | 3.4.3 | Implement URL construction | Base URL + path joining | 0.5h |\n75: | 3.4.4 | Implement header normalization | Case-insensitive header dict | 0.25h |\n76: | 3.4.5 | Implement query parameter handling | Query string construction | 0.25h |\n77: | 3.4.6 | Implement JSON body serialization | Content-Type handling | 0.25h |\n78: | 3.4.7 | Implement multipart/form-data support | File upload preparation | 0.5h |\n79: \n80: **Deliverable:** Request builder functional.\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## ST-3.5 — Response Wrapper\n85: \n86: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n87: |---|------|--------------|------|\n88: | 3.5.1 | Create `Response` class | Wraps httpx.Response | 0.25h |\n89: | 3.5.2 | Implement `.json()` method | JSON parsing with error handling | 0.25h |\n90: | 3.5.3 | Implement `.text` property | UTF-8 text decoding | 0.1h |\n91: | 3.5.4 | Implement `.status_code` property | HTTP status code | 0.1h |\n92: | 3.5.5 | Implement `.headers` property | Response headers | 0.1h |\n93: | 3.5.6 | Implement `.is_success` property | 2xx check | 0.1h |\n94: | 3.5.7 | Implement `.raise_for_status()` method | Exception on error status | 0.25h |\n95: | 3.5.8 | Create `StreamingResponse` class | Iterator for streaming data | 0.5h |\n96: \n97: **Deliverable:** Response wrapper complete.\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## ST-3.6 — Authentication Middleware\n102: \n103: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n104: |---|------|--------------|------|\n105: | 3.6.1 | Create `AuthMiddleware` ABC | Abstract apply method | 0.25h |\n106: | 3.6.2 | Implement `APIKeyAuth` | Header or query param API key | 0.5h |\n107: | 3.6.3 | Implement `BearerTokenAuth` | Authorization: Bearer header | 0.25h |\n108: | 3.6.4 | Implement `NoAuth` | No-op middleware | 0.1h |\n109: | 3.6.5 | Export auth classes from `auth.py` | Import works | 0.1h |\n110: | 3.6.6 | Add auth to request builder integration | Auth applied before sending | 0.25h |\n111: \n112: **Deliverable:** Auth middleware functional.\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## ST-3.7 — Retry Logic Implementation\n117: \n118: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n119: |---|------|--------------|------|\n120: | 3.7.1 | Create `RetryPolicy` class | Policy with config | 0.25h |\n121: | 3.7.2 | Implement exponential backoff | Delay calculation | 0.5h |\n122: | 3.7.3 | Implement linear backoff | Delay calculation | 0.25h |\n123: | 3.7.4 | Implement fixed backoff | Delay calculation | 0.25h |\n124: | 3.7.5 | Define retryable exceptions | ConnectionError, TimeoutError | 0.25h |\n125: | 3.7.6 | Define retryable status codes | 429, 5xx codes | 0.25h |\n126: | 3.7.7 | Create retry decorator/wrapper | Apply to client methods | 0.5h |\n127: | 3.7.8 | Add retry logging | Log attempts with level INFO | 0.25h |\n128: \n129: **Deliverable:** Retry logic functional.\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## ST-3.8 — HTTPClient Sync Implementation\n134: \n135: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n136: |---|------|--------------|------|\n137: | 3.8.1 | Create `HTTPClient` class | Class defined | 0.25h |\n138: | 3.8.2 | Implement `__init__()` with config | Attributes stored | 0.5h |\n139: | 3.8.3 | Implement sync `request()` method | Generic request handler | 0.5h |\n140: | 3.8.4 | Implement `get()` method | HTTP GET | 0.25h |\n141: | 3.8.5 | Implement `post()` method | HTTP POST | 0.25h |\n142: | 3.8.6 | Implement `put()` method | HTTP PUT | 0.25h |\n143: | 3.8.7 | Implement `patch()` method | HTTP PATCH | 0.25h |\n144: | 3.8.8 | Implement `delete()` method | HTTP DELETE | 0.25h |\n145: | 3.8.9 | Implement context manager | `__enter__`, `__exit__` | 0.25h |\n146: | 3.8.10 | Implement `close()` method | Connection cleanup | 0.25h |\n147: | 3.8.11 | Export from `client.py` | Import works | 0.1h |\n148: \n149: **Deliverable:** Sync HTTP client complete.\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## ST-3.9 — AsyncHTTPClient Implementation\n154: \n155: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n156: |---|------|--------------|------|\n157: | 3.9.1 | Create `AsyncHTTPClient` class | Class defined | 0.25h |\n158: | 3.9.2 | Implement `__init__()` with async config | Async client initialized | 0.5h |\n159: | 3.9.3 | Implement async `arequest()` method | Generic async request | 0.5h |\n160: | 3.9.4 | Implement `aget()` method | Async HTTP GET | 0.25h |\n161: | 3.9.5 | Implement `apost()` method | Async HTTP POST | 0.25h |\n162: | 3.9.6 | Implement `aput()` method | Async HTTP PUT | 0.25h |\n163: | 3.9.7 | Implement `apatch()` method | Async HTTP PATCH | 0.25h |\n164: | 3.9.8 | Implement `adelete()` method | Async HTTP DELETE | 0.25h |\n165: | 3.9.9 | Implement async context manager | `__aenter__`, `__aexit__` | 0.25h |\n166: | 3.9.10 | Implement `aclose()` method | Async cleanup | 0.25h |\n167: | 3.9.11 | Export from `client.py` | Import works | 0.1h |\n168: \n169: **Deliverable:** Async HTTP client complete.\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## ST-3.10 — Connection Pool Management\n174: \n175: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n176: |---|------|--------------|------|\n177: | 3.10.1 | Configure HTTPX connection limits | max_connections, max_keepalive | 0.5h |\n178: | 3.10.2 | Implement keep-alive handling | Connection reuse | 0.25h |\n179: | 3.10.3 | Implement connection cleanup | Proper resource release | 0.25h |\n180: | 3.10.4 | Add timeout configuration | connect, read, write timeouts | 0.25h |\n181: | 3.10.5 | Add SSL/TLS configuration | SSL context support | 0.25h |\n182: \n183: **Deliverable:** Connection pool management complete.\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## ST-3.11 — Unit Tests — Configuration\n188: \n189: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n190: |---|------|--------------|------|\n191: | 3.11.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/http/test_config.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n192: | 3.11.2 | Write `TestHTTPClientConfig` — valid data | Config creates | 0.5h |\n193: | 3.11.3 | Write `TestHTTPClientConfig` — invalid data | ValidationError raised | 0.5h |\n194: | 3.11.4 | Write `TestRetryConfig` — retry settings | Config creates correctly | 0.25h |\n195: | 3.11.5 | Write `TestRetryStrategy` — enum values | All strategies valid | 0.25h |\n196: \n197: **Deliverable:** Config tests pass.\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## ST-3.12 — Unit Tests — Request/Response\n202: \n203: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n204: |---|------|--------------|------|\n205: | 3.12.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/http/test_request.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n206: | 3.12.2 | Write `TestRequestBuilder` — URL construction | URLs built correctly | 0.5h |\n207: | 3.12.3 | Write `TestRequestBuilder` — header handling | Headers normalized | 0.25h |\n208: | 3.12.4 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/http/test_response.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n209: | 3.12.5 | Write `TestResponse` — JSON parsing | JSON decoded | 0.5h |\n210: | 3.12.6 | Write `TestResponse` — error detection | raise_for_status works | 0.25h |\n211: \n212: **Deliverable:** Request/response tests pass.\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## ST-3.13 — Unit Tests — Auth\n217: \n218: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n219: |---|------|--------------|------|\n220: | 3.13.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/http/test_auth.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n221: | 3.13.2 | Write `TestAPIKeyAuth` — header mode | API key in header | 0.5h |\n222: | 3.13.3 | Write `TestAPIKeyAuth` — query mode | API key in query | 0.5h |\n223: | 3.13.4 | Write `TestBearerTokenAuth` — token header | Bearer header set | 0.5h |\n224: | 3.13.5 | Write `TestNoAuth` — no modification | Request unchanged | 0.25h |\n225: \n226: **Deliverable:** Auth tests pass.\n227: \n228: ---\n229: \n230: ## ST-3.14 — Unit Tests — Retry Logic\n231: \n232: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n233: |---|------|--------------|------|\n234: | 3.14.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/http/test_retry.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n235: | 3.14.2 | Write `TestRetrySuccess` — succeeds after retry | Eventually passes | 0.5h |\n236: | 3.14.3 | Write `TestRetryExhausted` — fails after max | Raises after retries | 0.5h |\n237: | 3.14.4 | Write `TestRetryableErrors` — retries on 5xx | Retries on server errors | 0.5h |\n238: | 3.14.5 | Write `TestNonRetryableErrors` — no retry on 4xx | No retry on client errors | 0.5h |\n239: | 3.14.6 | Write `TestExponentialBackoff` — wait times | Increasing delays | 0.25h |\n240: \n241: **Deliverable:** Retry logic tests pass.\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ## ST-3.15 — Unit Tests — HTTPClient\n246: \n247: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n248: |---|------|--------------|------|\n249: | 3.15.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/http/test_client.py` | File exists with fixtures | 0.25h |\n250: | 3.15.2 | Write `TestHTTPClientInit` — initialization | Client creates with config | 0.5h |\n251: | 3.15.3 | Write `TestHTTPClientGet` — GET request | Request made correctly | 0.5h |\n252: | 3.15.4 | Write `TestHTTPClientPost` — POST request | POST with body works | 0.5h |\n253: | 3.15.5 | Write `TestHTTPClientError` — error handling | Raises on error status | 0.5h |\n254: | 3.15.6 | Mock transport with pytest-httpx | HTTP calls mocked | 0.5h |\n255: \n256: **Deliverable:** Sync client tests pass.\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n260: ## ST-3.16 — Unit Tests — AsyncHTTPClient\n261: \n262: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n263: |---|------|--------------|------|\n264: | 3.16.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/http/test_async_client.py` | File exists | 0.25h |\n265: | 3.16.2 | Write `TestAsyncHTTPClientInit` — async init | Client creates | 0.5h |\n266: | 3.16.3 | Write `TestAsyncGet` — async GET | Request works | 0.5h |\n267: | 3.16.4 | Write `TestAsyncPost` — async POST | POST with body works | 0.5h |\n268: | 3.16.5 | Write `TestAsyncConcurrent` — concurrent requests | Multiple parallel requests | 0.5h |\n269: | 3.16.6 | Mock async transport with respx | Async HTTP mocked | 0.5h |\n270: \n271: **Deliverable:** Async client tests pass.\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## ST-3.17 — Unit Tests — Exceptions\n276: \n277: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n278: |---|------|--------------|------|\n279: | 3.17.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/unit/http/test_exceptions.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n280: | 3.17.2 | Write `TestHTTPError` — base exception | Base class works | 0.25h |\n281: | 3.17.3 | Write `TestStatusCodeMapping` — 4xx errors | Correct exception raised | 0.5h |\n282: | 3.17.4 | Write `TestStatusCodeMapping` — 5xx errors | Correct exception raised | 0.5h |\n283: \n284: **Deliverable:** Exception tests pass.\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## ST-3.18 — Integration Tests\n289: \n290: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n291: |---|------|--------------|------|\n292: | 3.18.1 | Create `sdk-python/tests/integration/test_http_integration.py` | File with fixtures | 0.25h |\n293: | 3.18.2 | Test full request lifecycle | Request → Response | 1.0h |\n294: | 3.18.3 | Test against mock server | Mock responses | 0.5h |\n295: | 3.18.4 | Test error scenarios | Errors handled | 0.5h |\n296: | 3.18.5 | Test timeout handling | Timeout raises | 0.5h |\n297: | 3.18.6 | Test async full lifecycle | Async CRUD works | 1.0h |\n298: \n299: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass.\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ## ST-3.19 — Documentation\n304: \n305: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n306: |---|------|--------------|------|\n307: | 3.19.1 | Add module docstrings to all files | pydoc shows overview | 0.5h |\n308: | 3.19.2 | Add class docstrings to HTTPClient | Description and usage | 0.25h |\n309: | 3.19.3 | Add class docstrings to AsyncHTTPClient | Async usage | 0.25h |\n310: | 3.19.4 | Add docstrings to all public methods | Args, returns, raises | 0.5h |\n311: | 3.19.5 | Add type hints to all signatures | mypy passes | 0.5h |\n312: | 3.19.6 | Create usage examples