yAuth, BearerTokenAuth\"\n405: python -c \"from agentcube.http import HTTPError, ConnectionError, TimeoutError\"\n406: \n407: # Unit test verification\n408: pytest sdk-python/tests/unit/http/ -v\n409: \n410: # Integration tests\n411: pytest sdk-python/tests/integration/test_http_integration.py -v\n412: \n413: # Coverage report\n414: pytest --cov=agentcube.http --cov-report=term-missing\n415: \n416: # Lint verification\n417: ruff check sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/\n418: mypy sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/\n419: ```\n420: \n421: ---\n422: \n423: ## Definition of Done\n424: \n425: - [ ] All 140 tasks complete\n426: - [ ] Package installs successfully\n427: - [ ] HTTPClient importable from `agentcube.http`\n428: - [ ] AsyncHTTPClient importable from `agentcube.http`\n429: - [ ] All unit tests pass (>80% coverage)\n430: - [ ] All integration tests pass\n431: - [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n432: - [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n433: - [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n434: - [ ] Usage examples in README\n435: \n436: ---\n437: \n438: ## Dependencies\n439: \n440: - `httpx>=0.25.0` — HTTP client (sync + async)\n441: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation (already in pyproject.toml)\n442: - `tenacity>=8.2.0` — Retry logic\n443: - `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework (already present)\n444: - `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0` — Async test support\n445: - `pytest-httpx>=0.22.0` — HTTP mocking for tests\n446: - `respx>=0.20.0` — HTTPX async mocking\n447: \n448: ---\n449: \n450: ## Notes\n451: \n452: - Follow existing code style in sdk-python\n453: - Ensure type hints on all public methods\n454: - Use `httpx` for both sync and async HTTP (unified API)\n455: - Keep configuration immutable where possible\n456: - Document all raised exceptions in docstrings\n457: - HTTP client should be reusable across multiple high-level clients\n458: \n459: ---\n460: \n461: *AR-029 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 461 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-029\n> **Module:** `sdk-python`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement the low-level HTTP client foundation for the sdk-python module. This component provides a robust, reusable HTTP client layer that handles connection management, request/response handling, authentication, retry logic, and error handling. It serves as the transport foundation for all high-level SDK clients.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.1 — Project Structure Setup\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775908285728,"end":1775908285757}}}}
