{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775908738079,"sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","part":{"id":"prt_d7c62cc66001SkwEI4Qd3vK68Y","messageID":"msg_d7c627854001qOddWvL208yElB","sessionID":"ses_2839e4390ffejbecz7fZUCpLLi","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailing-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md","content":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-029\n> **Module:** `sdk-python`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement the low-level HTTP client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK. This AR delivers three specific HTTP clients (`ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`) and supporting utilities for connection pooling, authentication, timeout handling, and session header management.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.1 — HTTP Session Factory\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.1.1 | Create `agentcube/utils/http.py` module | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.2 | Implement `create_session(pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Returns `requests.Session` with adapters | 0.5h |\n| 3.1.3 | Mount `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` protocol | `session.adapters[\"http://\"]` exists | 0.25h |\n| 3.1.4 | Mount `HTTPAdapter` for `https://` protocol | `session.adapters[\"https://\"]` exists | 0.25h |\n| 3.1.5 | Default pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10 | Adapter config matches defaults | 0.25h |\n| 3.1.6 | Custom pool configuration passes through | `create_session(20, 50)` sets correct values | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** `create_session()` utility functional.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.2 — Token Reading Utility\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.2.1 | Implement `read_token_from_file(file_path)` | Returns stripped file content | 0.25h |\n| 3.2.2 | Return em